"n.骑师；v.用计谋获取 【英】 n. 骑师; v.用计谋获取(manoeu vre to gain an avantage) 【例】 jockey for position n. 职业赛马骑师 【记】jockey = joy＋key, 主要是为了娱乐－职业赛马骑师Jockey是乔基男性三角裤的商标名, 被职业赛马骑师广为采用. 【记】音：找key，找钥匙，来开动操作汽车或机器；电台或舞厅里所说的DJ，这个J就是jockey，disc jockey 音乐CD的操作员 jockey (n.)  1520s, ""boy, fellow,"" originally a Scottish proper name, variant of Jack. The meaning ""person who rides horses in races"" first attested 1660s. jockey (v.)  1708, ""trick, outwit, gain advantage,"" from jockey (n.) perhaps from its former additional sense of ""horse trader"" (1680s). Meaning ""to ride a horse in a race"" is from 1767. Related: Jockeyed; jockeying."
